race.description: Tabtouch - Have You Got The Touch Handicap (C3)
race.comment: OPAL TANGO (10) sat on the speed last start over this course and distance but couldn't go on with the job, beaten 3L. That looked a relatively strong CL1 however and now up in grade she drops in weight. The better draw today is a big tick and she's expected to turn in a bold performance. GRANDAD'S ADICTION (3) stuck on strongly over 1400m at Belmont last time out, beaten just 0.6L. Steve Parnham now hops in the saddle in a good push for his chances. Looks suited by the rise in trip now and can put his best foot forward. ALMAYA (5) got the job done by 0.4L last start with the second horse coming out and winning last Wednesday. This looks to shape similarly today from a decent alley. Can repeat the dose. MONTY ZOOMER (6) was too good from the front at Kalgoorlie and can go back-to-back with Pike replacing the apprentice hoop. KNOCKONEBACK (8) is racing well and has to be included.
